Brazos showcase halls pick up maintenance and fit-out work.  The other two megacorps treat the award as a deliberate snub — useful leverage if we meant to pick a side.

@local_wealthy
view-if: contract_fair_chain_complete = 0
title: Local wealthy contractors

Shareholder-adjacent workshops and Docks rentiers both bid for the same municipal line items.  Either cluster works; the city's moneyed strata gossip about the award no matter which district hosts the signing ceremony.

- @wealthy_docks: Award through Docks firms
- @wealthy_aurora: Award through Aurora firms
- @return

@wealthy_docks
title: Award through Docks firms
subtitle: Prosperity in the Docks; shareholders citywide take notice
on-arrival: {!
contract_wealthy_docks = 1;
Q.rich_bump = 0.05;
if (typeof Q.addAsset === 'function') {
    Q.addAsset({ id: 'docks_wealthy_contract_office', name: 'Docks shareholder contract office', district: 'Docks', ownerType: 'stratum', owner: 'rich', kind: 'office', major: false });
}
if (typeof Q.applyStratumProsperityBumps === 'function') { Q.applyStratumProsperityBumps(); }
if (typeof Q.bumpDistrictProsperity === 'function') { Q.bumpDistrictProsperity('Docks', 0.05); }
if (typeof Q.queueBudgetExpense === 'function') { Q.queueBudgetExpense(3, 'contract_award', 'Municipal contract award'); }
!}

Docks shareholders pocket the prime subcontracts while their cousins in other districts still benefit from the spending ripple.  The old money crowd approves of government that pays on time.

